# PR-BF: Long cache + immutable on the email logo PNGs.
# Gmail's image proxy refuses to display images whose revalidation
# fails (rather than serving stale), and the default
# `cache-control: max-age=0, must-revalidate` from CF Static Assets
# means every proxy fetch is a revalidation attempt. With max-age=1y
# + immutable the proxy caches once and never re-validates — which
# is what we want for a brandmark that essentially never changes
# (and would get a new filename if it did).
/logo-email-mark.png
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/logo-email.png
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
